    <abstract>
      <t>Modern networks require adaptive traffic manipulation including Traffic Engineering (TE), load balancing, flow control and protection etc. to support applications like AI training and real-time services. A good and timely understanding of network operational status, such as congestion and failures, can help to improve utilization, reduce latency, and enable faster response to critical events. This document describes the existing problems and why the IETF may need a new set of network notification related solutions to support any high-throughput, low-latency and lossless application.</t>
